ning:**\n\n1. Pick a checkpoint (red node), your two images, and a video path on the Frame Saver.\n2. In the Prompt Notebook, ctrl/cmd+click to select 2+ prompts.\n3. In Apply LoRA Set, pick a saved state (make one with the Controller corner below).\n4. Run a few times in **Collect** to fill the grid, then flip the grid to **Emit** for the big run.\n\n**Run count = loras x 3 strengths (0.0/0.5/1.0) x grid images x prompts.** Start small; raise the sweep increment later. Output lands in `output/eps_demo/<lora_strength>/<prompt name>_*.png`."],"color":"#432","bgcolor":"#653"},{"id":22,"type":"MarkdownNote","pos":[-1280,-160],"size":[380,260],"flags":{},"order":8,"mode":0,"inputs":[],"outputs":[],"properties":{},"widgets_values":["## 1. Sources -> Switcher\n\nThree image sources: two stills + a video frame. Toggle rows on the Switcher to choose which feed the pipeline; toggled-off branches never run. All enabled images flow on (lists merge element-wise)."],"color":"#432","bgcolor":"#653"},{"id":23,"type":"MarkdownNote","pos":[-460,-60],"size":[380,200],"flags":{},"order":9,"mode":0,"inputs":[],"outputs":[],"properties":{},"widgets_values":["## 2. Resolution -> Grid\n\nEvery source is normalized to fit 1024. In **Collect** each run records into the grid (and passes through). Flip to **Emit** to fan the whole collection out (buffer + anything wired, e.g. 10+1=11)."],"color":"#432","bgcolor":"#653"},{"id":24,"type":"MarkdownNote","pos":[-40,140],"size":[400,220],"flags":{},"order":10,"mode":0,"inputs":[],"outputs":[],"properties":{},"widgets_values":["## 3. Pairs\n\nCross Product pairs EVERY grid image with EVERY selected prompt (2 x 4 = 8) - ComfyUI alone would zip them index-by-index instead. Entry names ride along for folder naming."],"color":"#432","bgcolor":"#653"},{"id":25,"type":"MarkdownNote","pos":[-820,1560],"size":[400,240],"flags":{},"order":11,"mode":0,"inputs":[],"outputs":[],"properties":{},"widgets_values":["## 4. Lora path\n\nApply LoRA Set reads a saved state (shared library folder). LoRA Sweep fans it out per strength step. The Controller corner captures states from the Power Lora Loader; Save renames in place, New State creates."],"color":"#432","bgcolor":"#653"},{"id":26,"type":"MarkdownNote","pos":[480,340],"size":[420,260],"flags":{},"order":12,"mode":0,"inputs":[],"outputs":[],"properties":{},"widgets_values":["## 5. Cross Sweep -> generate\n\nSweep steps x pairs, strength-major: all pairs at 0.0, then 0.5, then 1.0. `save_prefix` -> SaveImage files each strength into its own folder: `eps_demo/<lora>_0.5/<PromptName>_00001_.png`. Fixed seed 42 repeats across runs (clean A/B); denoise 0.6 img2img so the input images matter."],"color":"#432","bgcolor":"#653"}],"links":[[1,1,0,4,0,"IMAGE"],[2,2,0,4,2,"IMAGE"],[3,3,0,4,3,"IMAGE"],[4,4,0,5,0,"IMAGE"],[5,5,1,6,0,"IMAGE"],[6,6,0,8,0,"IMAGE"],[7,7,0,8,1,"STRING"],[8,7,1,8,2,"STRING"],[9,9,0,10,0,"MODEL"],[10,9,1,10,1,"CLIP"],[11,10,0,11,0,"MODEL"],[12,10,1,11,2,"CLIP"],[13,10,2,11,1,"LORA_STACK"],[14,11,0,12,0,"MODEL"],[15,11,1,12,1,"CLIP"],[16,11,2,12,2,"STRING"],[17,8,0,12,3,"IMAGE"],[18,8,1,12,4,"STRING"],[19,8,2,12,5,"STRING"],[20,12,1,13,0,"CLIP"],[21,12,3,13,1,"STRING"],[22,12,1,14,0,"CLIP"],[23,12,2,15,0,"IMAGE"],[24,9,2,15,1,"VAE"],[25,12,0,16,0,"MODEL"],[26,13,0,16,1,"CONDITIONING"],[27,14,0,16,2,"CONDITIONING"],[28,15,0,16,3,"LATENT"],[29,16,0,17,0,"LATENT"],[30,9,2,17,1,"VAE"],[31,17,0,18,0,"IMAGE"],[32,12,4,18,1,"STRING"]],"groups":[{"id":1,"title":"1 - Sources & Switcher","bounding":[-1800,-220,940,1300],"color":"#3f789e","flags":{}},{"id":2,"title":"2 - Normalize & Collect","bounding":[-930,60,880,700],"color":"#88A","flags":{}},{"id":3,"title":"3 - Prompts & Pairs","bounding":[-930,560,1300,460],"color":"#8A8","flags":{}},{"id":4,"title":"4 - Loras & Sweep","bounding":[-1800,1120,2180,380],"color":"#b58b2a","flags":{}},{"id":5,"title":"5 - Cross Sweep & Generate","bounding":[380,260,1900,1300],"color":"#a1309b","flags":{}},{"id":6,"title":"State Contro